The program superstring can be provided an input file
to read the strings and evaluate the string that can
be formed with maximum number of other substrings.

The program will print the string the first three levels
 by default, can be changed to print additional by changing
macro MAX_LEVELS_TO_DISPLAY i.e the strings with maximum number of 
substrings, the string with one less than maximum number of substrings and so 
on.

the program optionally takes an argument -enable_debug
to enable debug.

eg 

$ superstring -enable_debug
Enter the name of the input file
wordslist

The maximum number of substrings in a string is 3

String with 3 substrings
shz::s::h::z

String with 2 substrings
aah::aa::h

String with 1
